data.title: school Archives
data.meta_description: A school is a place where children are educated. You usually refer to this place as school when you are talking about the time that children spend there and the activities that they do there.

Iroquois Ridge High School is a public high school school located in the Joshua Creek neighbourhood of Oakville, Ontario, Canada. It offers classroom instruction for grades 9-12, and is a member of the Dufferin-Peel Catholic District School Board. The school opened in 2003 at a temporary location in Streetsville, Mississauga.
